-- Statement: DROP SCHEMA
-- Grammar rule: dropSchemaStatement (TSql170.g)
-- Doc: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/t-sql/statements/drop-schema-transact-sql

-- From TSql170.g:
dropSchemaStatement:
    Schema
    ( If Exists )?
    schemaObjectThreePartName
    ( Cascade | Restrict )?
    ;

-- Note: Schema name with more than one part must be followed by either
-- Restrict or Cascade (SQL 2000 syntax).

-- From Microsoft docs:
-- Syntax for SQL Server and Azure SQL Database
DROP SCHEMA [ IF EXISTS ] schema_name

-- Syntax for Azure Synapse Analytics and Parallel Data Warehouse
DROP SCHEMA schema_name
